summary: Quarterfinals of the Champions League: five things to know about Matthijs de Ligt (Ajax Amsterdam)
title: Quarterfinals of the Champions League: five things to know about Matthijs de Ligt (Ajax Amsterdam)
body:
The young captain (19 years) of Ajax Amsterdam, whose name is associated with many foreign clubs (Barcelona, ​​Real Madrid), will get his first quarter-final Champions League this Wednesday night against Juventus.

A vital member of the Ajax squad (39 games in all competitions), the athletic central defender (1.88m, 89kg) Matthijs de Ligt has a resounding career start with his training club. Aligned 22 times in European Cups, he took part in his first professional season in the final of the Europa League lost in 2017 against Manchester United (0-2).

Imposing in the aerial game and dress raiser, the young Dutch is endowed with unusual technical qualities. A style of play reminiscent of Barcelona’s Gerard Piqué. Like him, he started in midfield and had to back down over time. Some Spanish media say that the Catalan club has made the defender of Amsterdam a priority to densify its workforce. The Dutch international would emulate his team-mate Frenkie de Jong, who will join Barça in the 2019-2020 season. In the meantime, here are five things to know about Matthijs de Ligt.

He is a model of maturity


At the age of 9 at Ajax Amsterdam, Matthijs de Ligt made all his scales there before making his debut with the first team in 2016. Over-rated throughout his training, he regularly crossed the line. path of his current teammates Frenkie de Jong or Kasper Dolberg.

Praised for its maturity on the fields but also outside, Matthijs de Ligt astonishes by his faculty not to get rid of the ball during the weak times. So he is called for the first time in the professional group on September 21, 2016 for the match against Willem II. Date when he played his first match in the shoes of a holder and scored the first goal of his career. At 17, Matthijs de Ligt becomes the second youngest scorer in club history behind Clarence Seedorf.

“He will be the best central defender in the world in two years”

 Ronald Koeman


The youngest international Dutch
The notable feat of arms of Mattijs De Ligt takes place on March 25, 2017 when he knows his first selection at the Oranje against Bulgaria (0-2). At 17 years and 225 days, he becomes the youngest Dutch international to start an official meeting. Today he has 15 caps and is now part of the team. “He will be the best central defender in the world in two years,” said coach Ronald Koeman.

He sickened Kylian Mbappé

One League of Nations meeting between the Netherlands and France (November 16, 2018, 2-0 win for Oranje), he again reported neutralizing all offensive French. The leader of the attack tricolor, Kylian Mbappé, had failed to find the flaw, routinely defeat the defender of Ajax. A credit score of 8 by L'Equipe, Matthijs de Ligt seduced all observers: what to make a name on the international scene.

He was elected Golden Boy 2018


By succeeding Kylian Mbappé at the 2018 Golden Boy, Matthijs de Ligt has risen to the rank of best young European player. He became the first defender to win this honorary award usually given to attackers. The market value of the Dutch international has steadily increased and places the Ajax player in the rank of the most bankable defender in Europe.

He is Barça compatible


Equipped with a good vision of the game and not hesitating to be aggressive in the duels, Matthijs de Ligt is the archetype of the modern central defender. FC Barcelona was interested in him during the last winter transfer window in preparation for next season. “He’s the captain of Ajax, he comes from their school, that is to say the school of FC Barcelona because it means he has a lot of technical and tactical qualities,” said Ronald Koeman . The Marca newspaper talks about the Dutch player as an alternative to Gerard Piqué.

If rumors are moving in this direction, no formalization has been announced for the moment. Behind the scenes, the leaders of Ajax Amsterdam seem to be open to negotiation, aware of the attractiveness of major European clubs. In addition to FC Barcelona, ​​Juventus and Real Madrid are particularly interested in the profile of the player, who should not be long in leaving Amsterdam.

Nogometaši Tottenhama i Liverpoola ostvarili su pobjede u prvim susretima četvrtfinala Lige prvaka. Spursi su na svom novom stadionu pobijedili Manchester City sa 1-0, dok je Liverpool na Anfieldu porazio Porto sa 2-0. Uzvratne utakmice su 17. travnja u Manchesteru i Portu.
